            Who is liable when a rideshare driver causes an accident?
            <span class="text-primary group-open:rotate-180 transition">â–¼</span>
          </summary>
          <p class="mt-4 text-gray-600">
            Liability depends on the driver's status at the time of the accident. When a passenger is in the vehicle or the driver is en route to a pickup, the rideshare company's $1 million commercial insurance typically covers the accident. Both the driver and the rideshare company may be held liable depending on the circumstances.
          </p>
        </details>
        
